                            <comment id="10355" author="kjessup" created="Mon, 21 Dec 2015 10:28:49 -0500"  >&lt;p&gt;Correct and thank you for the feedback.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I added &lt;tt&gt;WebRequest.postBodyBytes&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;WebRequest.postBodyString&lt;/tt&gt; to provide access to this data as either &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;UInt8&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; or String, respectively.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I tested using URL Routing example &amp;amp; curl on the cli and was able to grab the raw data as expected.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;curl --data &quot;&lt;/p&gt;
{\&quot;id\&quot;:123}
&lt;p&gt;&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;http://0.0.0.0:8181/raw&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://0.0.0.0:8181/raw&lt;/a&gt; --header &quot;Content-Type:application/json&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thank you!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
